title: Eagles wide receivers Nelson Agholor, Riley Cooper both miss practice
text:
Eagles wide receivers Nelson Agholor, Riley Cooper both miss practice THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   4:47   4:47   
People: 
Pennsylvania (896) 
PHILADELPHIA â€” Philadelphia Eagles wide receivers Nelson Agholor and Riley Cooper both sat out of practice for the second consecutive day on Thursday, putting in doubt their availability for Sunday night's game against the Carolina Panthers. 
Agholor, the 2015 first-round draft pick from the University of Southern California, suffered a leg injury when the Eagles beat the New Orleans Saints on Oct. 11. He missed Monday's win over the New York Giants. 
Cooper suffered a knee injury in that win over the Giants, although he did return to the game.
